The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Pharma pay hike to be highest
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Pharma pay hike to be highest
                            
	New Delhi, June 17 (PTI): Employees in the pharmaceutical sector can expect an average pay hike of 13 per cent in 2010-11 amid robust business growth, according to HR services provider Ma Foi Randstad.        
	According to Ma Foi Randstads survey on employment trends, various sectors in the country are expected to witness hikes in the range of 8-13 per cent during this fiscal.        
	The pharmaceutical sector is expected to see the highest salary increase of 13.2 per cent on an average this fiscal.        
	Real estate and healthcare are projected to see hikes of 12.1 per cent, while the energy space may see pay grow 12.8 per cent on an average.        
	Other sectors expected to see double-digit hikes include education and consultancy (12.6 per cent), IT amp; IT-enabled services (11.1 per cent) and hospitality (10.6 per cent).                                                                                                                                                   
